time required: 40 minutes
---

Preheat oven to 450 degrees. Wash and dry all produce. Cut @Yukon Gold Potatoes{12%ounce} into ½-inch-thick wedges. Peel and slice half the @Red Onion{1} into ¼-inch-thick rings, keeping them intact (slice whole onion for 4 servings); mince a slice until you have 2 tsp (4 tsp for 4). Thinly slice @Roma Tomato{1} and @Dill Pickle{1} into rounds. Finely chop a few pickle slices until you have 1 TBSP (2 TBSP for 4). Mince @Chili Pepper{1}. Halve @Potato Buns{2}.

Toss potatoes on a #baking sheet{} with a large drizzle of @vegetable oil{4%teaspoon}, half the @Fry Seasoning{1%tablespoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}. Roast on top rack until crispy, ~{20-25%minutes}. Meanwhile, in a #medium bowl{}, combine @Ground Beef{10%ounce}, remaining Fry Seasoning, salt (we used ¾ tsp; 1 1/2 tsp for 4 servings), and pepper. Form into two patties (four for 4), each slightly wider than a burger bun.

In a #small bowl{}, combine @Ketchup{2%tablespoon}, chopped pickle, half the @Sour Cream{4%tablespoon}, and up to half the minced onion to taste. Season with salt and pepper. In a separate small bowl, combine @Cheddar Cheese{1/2%cup}, @Mayonnaise{2%tablespoon}, remaining sour cream, 1 tsp minced onion (2 tsp for 4 servings), and a pinch of chili to taste. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a drizzle of oil in a #large pan{} over high heat. Add onion slices in a single layer (try to keep rings intact but don't worry if some fall apart); season with salt and pepper. Cook until lightly charred, ~{1-2%minutes} per side. Transfer to a #plate{}.

Heat a drizzle of oil in same pan over medium-high heat. Add patties and cook to desired doneness, ~{3-5%minutes} per side. In the last 1-2 minutes of cooking, top each patty with cheddar spread; cover pan until cheese has melted. Place @Butter{1%tablespoon} in a #small microwave-safe bowl{}; microwave until melted, ~{30%seconds}. Brush onto cut sides of buns. Carefully place buns cut sides up on top rack of oven until toasted, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Fill buns with patties and as much tomato, charred onion, and sliced pickle as you like. Divide between plates with potato wedges. Serve with special sauce and any remaining sliced pickle on the side.